00:47:33,300 --> 00:47:35,400
Hey, I'm over here
behind the fat guy.

773
00:47:35,500 --> 00:47:37,900
- Where's our seat?
- Right over here, Michelle.

774
00:47:38,000 --> 00:47:39,300
Great, we're in front!

775
00:47:39,400 --> 00:47:40,800
Peanuts here.

776
00:47:40,900 --> 00:47:42,600
Stale, overpriced peanuts.

777
00:47:44,100 --> 00:47:46,600
Want your stale peanuts?

778
00:47:47,700 --> 00:47:49,000
Yeah?

779
00:47:49,100 --> 00:47:51,700
Wow. All right, all right, terrific.

780
00:47:51,800 --> 00:47:55,500
We've got 2,000 seats sold already.
It's gonna be a great opening night.

781
00:47:55,600 --> 00:47:57,600
For a new league,
this is fantastic.

782
00:47:57,700 --> 00:47:59,500
I'm so excited, I'm gonna die.

783
00:47:59,600 --> 00:48:01,200
Hey, who's that guy on the ice?

784
00:48:01,300 --> 00:48:03,800
I like his suit!

785
00:48:03,900 --> 00:48:08,500
Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to an historic evening,

786
00:48:08,600 --> 00:48:14,400
the debut of the World Wide
Women' Hockey League,

787
00:48:14,500 --> 00:48:17,300
a night we will all long remember.

788
00:48:17,400 --> 00:48:22,600
And without any further ado,
I give you the Almighty Swans!

789
00:48:27,400 --> 00:48:29,800
We love you, Swans!

790
00:48:29,900 --> 00:48:34,100
And these are
your Fearsome Foxes!

791
00:48:51,300 --> 00:48:52,500
Come on!

792
00:48:56,400 --> 00:48:58,500
I'm so proud of you, Frank.

793
00:48:58,600 --> 00:49:00,900
Although I still think
you were a great lawyer,

794
00:49:01,000 --> 00:49:03,200
I think you've finally
found your niche.

795
00:49:45,100 --> 00:49:46,700
Keep your shirt on! Come on.

796
00:49:46,800 --> 00:49:48,400
Let's get in the game.

797
00:50:49,700 --> 00:50:51,400
- Get it!
- Get the puck! Get the puck!

798
00:50:51,500 --> 00:50:52,500
Move it! Move it!

799
00:50:53,700 --> 00:50:55,300
- That' what I'm talkin' about!
- Toss it away!

800
00:50:55,400 --> 00:50:56,300
You got it!

801
00:50:57,800 --> 00:50:58,700
Let' go!

802
00:51:01,600 --> 00:51:02,900
Let's go!

803
00:51:25,300 --> 00:51:27,500
No! Wendy!

804
00:51:29,900 --> 00:51:32,400
Wendy, baby!
I'm coming, baby! I'm coming!

805
00:52:00,200 --> 00:52:03,100
Oh, my God, oh, my God,
this is so incredible!

806
00:52:03,200 --> 00:52:05,100
Glenda, they need me.

807
00:52:11,900 --> 00:52:17,000
O say, can you see

808
00:52:17,100 --> 00:52:20,900
By the dawn' early light

809
00:52:21,000 --> 00:52:24,900
What so proudly we hailed

810
00:52:25,000 --> 00:52:29,100
At the twilight' last gleaming?

811
00:52:29,200 --> 00:52:31,400
Whose broad...

812
00:52:35,000 --> 00:52:37,100
Come on, we got
a hockey game to finish here!

813
00:52:54,300 --> 00:52:57,400
Fans, remember, while you're waiting
for the next period to begin,

814
00:52:57,500 --> 00:52:59,900
please visit one
of our refreshment stations...

815
00:53:00,000 --> 00:53:02,900
If that's the worst thing
that happens tonight, we'll be okay.

816
00:53:03,000 --> 00:53:04,800
...all major credit cards
are accepted.

817
00:53:08,100 --> 00:53:09,400
Frank Hopper?

818
00:53:09,500 --> 00:53:10,600
Yeah.

819
00:53:10,700 --> 00:53:13,300
Mr. Hopper,
I'm Detective Feretti, Fraud Division.

820
00:53:13,400 --> 00:53:15,100
I have a warrant for your arrest.

821
00:53:15,200 --> 00:53:16,200
What?

822
00:53:16,300 --> 00:53:17,300
I'm his attorney.

823
00:53:17,400 --> 00:53:19,500
On what charges?
He just broke that fight up.

824
00:53:19,600 --> 00:53:20,900
Nothing to do with that,
Counselor.

825
00:53:21,000 --> 00:53:22,700
It's grand larceny,
credit card fraud,

826
00:53:22,800 --> 00:53:25,300
seeking and gaining credit fraudulently,
misuse of bank funds,

827
00:53:25,400 --> 00:53:28,000
and misrepresentation
with intent to defraud.

828
00:53:28,100 --> 00:53:29,100
What?

829
00:53:30,500 --> 00:53:34,000
Congratulations, Mr. Hopper.
You've won top honors this month.

830
00:53:35,600 --> 00:53:37,300
So this is how you did it.

831
00:53:39,000 --> 00:53:40,900
Mr. Dependable.

832
00:53:41,000 --> 00:53:42,200
Jessica, wait a minute.

833
00:53:49,200 --> 00:53:52,100
- Thanks for bailing me...
- Not a word, Frank, not a peep.

834
00:53:52,200 --> 00:53:53,800
Boy, you really did it this time.

835
00:53:53,900 --> 00:53:55,700
Failure wasn't
good enough for you, was it?

836
00:53:55,800 --> 00:53:57,800
You had to try your hand
at crime as well!

837
00:53:59,300 --> 00:54:01,600
Do you have any idea
how many laws you broke?

838
00:54:01,700 --> 00:54:03,600
If you charge
an exorbitant amount of money

839
00:54:03,700 --> 00:54:06,700
knowing you don't have the means
of paying that back, it's fraud.

840
00:54:06,700 --> 00:54:08,800
It's a crime,
or the credit card companies

841
00:54:08,900 --> 00:54:11,800
would like to prove that as a warning
to entrepreneurs like you.

842
00:54:11,900 --> 00:54:13,900
And they say you
falsified a credit application!

843
00:54:14,000 --> 00:54:17,700
I didn't know... the cashier told me
it was some kind of survey.

844
00:54:17,800 --> 00:54:19,600
She got two dollars and I got a pen.

845
00:54:19,700 --> 00:54:21,000
Wow! You got a pen!

846
00:54:21,100 --> 00:54:22,600
But then I got the card,

847
00:54:22,700 --> 00:54:25,600
and I had the idea for the league,
but it was working!

848
00:54:26,700 --> 00:54:28,600
You're gonna need
a trial lawyer now.

849
00:54:28,800 --> 00:54:30,800
I'm gonna have
to think about this.

850
00:54:35,700 --> 00:54:37,800
No, no, no.

851
00:54:37,900 --> 00:54:39,000
No.

852
00:54:40,000 --> 00:54:41,600
Please, Jessica.

853
00:54:41,700 --> 00:54:42,900
He lied to me,

854
00:54:43,000 --> 00:54:45,700
and I fell for the whole
song and dance all over again.

855
00:54:45,800 --> 00:54:46,900
I know.

856
00:54:47,000 --> 00:54:50,300
He's a conniver, an opportunist,
a failure, a loser,

857
00:54:50,400 --> 00:54:52,200
a freeloader, a parasite, a bum!

858
00:54:52,300 --> 00:54:54,300
A deceitful, lying rat.

859
00:54:54,500 --> 00:54:55,600
So he's not perfect.

860
00:54:57,000 --> 00:54:59,500
He ripped off the credit card companies...
how bad can he be?

861
00:55:01,800 --> 00:55:02,700
I can't do it.

862
00:55:02,800 --> 00:55:05,600
These bastards are playing hardball.

863
00:55:05,700 --> 00:55:07,600
They're gonna
make Frank the poster boy

864
00:55:07,700 --> 00:55:09,800
for 40 million credit card
delinquents.

865
00:55:09,900 --> 00:55:12,100
There's no way I would
ask you to do this, but...

866
00:55:12,700 --> 00:55:14,900
he's looking
at doing jail time, Jess.

867
00:55:18,900 --> 00:55:20,600
Why can't you represent me?

868
00:55:20,700 --> 00:55:23,000
I draw up contracts
and have drinks with people.

869
00:55:23,100 --> 00:55:24,600
You could be going away
for a long time!

870
00:55:24,700 --> 00:55:26,300
I'll get a public defender.

871
00:55:26,400 --> 00:55:28,000
You're playing with the big boys.

872
00:55:28,200 --> 00:55:30,500
You need the best lawyer you can get,
and Jessica is the best!

873
00:55:30,600 --> 00:55:33,300
I just get a feeling
she thinks I'm a con man and a liar.

874
00:55:35,300 --> 00:55:37,200
And what makes you think that?

875
00:55:38,700 --> 00:55:39,900
She told me.

876
00:55:41,300 --> 00:55:44,300
I know you think you've
totally blown it with Jessica.

877
00:55:44,400 --> 00:55:48,000
I know you think that there's
nothing you could do to make it right.

878
00:55:48,100 --> 00:55:52,000
All that is true, but put it behind you.
She's doing this as a favor for me.

879
00:55:52,100 --> 00:55:56,300
The kids put some stuff from
their lunches for you to take to prison.

880
00:55:58,000 --> 00:55:59,400
Thanks, Nicky.

881
00:56:00,400 --> 00:56:01,800
Okay, you win.

882
00:56:04,000 --> 00:56:06,300
Before we start, I wanna get
one thing straight.

883
00:56:06,400 --> 00:56:09,900
I'm the lawyer, and you're the client
and nothing else. Got it?

884
00:56:11,900 --> 00:56:13,000
Yeah, I got it.

885
00:56:17,700 --> 00:56:19,800
He wants to call you
as his only witness.

886
00:56:19,900 --> 00:56:21,300
He. Who's he?

887
00:56:21,400 --> 00:56:23,900
Norman Brown.
He's prosecuting the case.

888
00:56:24,000 --> 00:56:25,900
Your old boyfriend
Norman Brown?

889
00:56:26,900 --> 00:56:27,900
He'll kill us.

890
00:56:28,000 --> 00:56:31,000
He can't make you testify, and I'm
not gonna let him put you on the stand.

891
00:56:31,100 --> 00:56:32,700
What'll he do if I don't testify?

892
00:56:32,800 --> 00:56:35,800
Probably call Leona,
Carl, maybe Nick.

893
00:56:35,900 --> 00:56:37,500
Nick's 9 years old.

894
00:56:37,600 --> 00:56:39,700
He'll wanna prove
you have no work ethic.

895
00:56:39,800 --> 00:56:42,500
I'll testify. I could prove
I have no work ethic.

896
00:56:42,600 --> 00:56:44,000
I don't want you to testify.

897
00:56:44,100 --> 00:56:45,500
I'm not putting him through this.

898
00:56:46,600 --> 00:56:47,800
They wanna make an example of you.

899
00:56:47,900 --> 00:56:49,900
They wanna put
your picture in the paper

900
00:56:50,000 --> 00:56:54,800
and prove that credit card debt
is real debt, not just paper debt.

901
00:56:54,900 --> 00:56:56,600
And then they'll settle.

902
00:56:56,700 --> 00:56:58,900
What'll happen to the league?

903
00:56:59,000 --> 00:57:00,500
Frank, the league is over.

904
00:57:01,500 --> 00:57:02,800
It's kaput.

905
00:57:04,000 --> 00:57:05,500
At least you won't do jail time.

906
00:57:14,000 --> 00:57:15,100
We gotta hurry up.

907
00:57:15,200 --> 00:57:17,600
Let's redeem the girls.

908
00:57:17,700 --> 00:57:18,900
I'll testify!

909
00:57:21,700 --> 00:57:24,600
Nearly all of us, at one time
or another, have been in debt...

910
00:57:25,200 --> 00:57:30,200
but being in debt indicates a desire
and an expectancy to pay.

911
00:57:30,300 --> 00:57:33,300
This man had no such delusions.

912
00:57:33,400 --> 00:57:36,700
The assistant district attorney
wants you to believe that my client

913
00:57:36,800 --> 00:57:38,600
has lived in failure...

914
00:57:38,800 --> 00:57:42,400
Failure, delusion... and now crime.

915
00:57:42,500 --> 00:57:46,000
He has lived in dreams
and imagination.

916
00:57:46,100 --> 00:57:49,900
It is a criminal offense to acquire
a credit card by falsifying an application.

917
00:57:50,000 --> 00:57:52,600
But some of the greatest advances
of mankind have come

918
00:57:52,700 --> 00:57:54,800
from the dreams
of those who were laughed at.

919
00:57:54,800 --> 00:57:57,400
...assume credit card debt,
knowing full well

920
00:57:57,500 --> 00:58:02,000
you do not have the ability
or the intention of repaying that debt.

921
00:58:02,100 --> 00:58:04,600
The assistant district attorney
wants you to believe...

922
00:58:04,700 --> 00:58:07,600
He is nothing more
than a common criminal.

923
00:58:07,700 --> 00:58:11,700
He is not, for if he is a criminal,
we'd better start building more jails,

924
00:58:11,800 --> 00:58:17,000
because as we sit here, there are
40 million people in this country,

925
00:58:17,100 --> 00:58:21,000
40 million people, who are in debt
to credit card companies.

926
00:58:21,100 --> 00:58:23,500
I shall call only one witness
during this trial...

927
00:58:23,600 --> 00:58:26,000
the defendant himself,
Frank Hopper,

928
00:58:26,100 --> 00:58:29,500
for he is his own condemnation.

929
00:58:30,300 --> 00:58:31,300
Thank you.

930
00:58:32,800 --> 00:58:35,000
Mr. Hopper, where
were you employed

931
00:58:35,100 --> 00:58:39,100
when you signed your application
for your first credit card?

932
00:58:39,300 --> 00:58:40,900
I was between projects.

933
00:58:41,100 --> 00:58:42,700
Oh, really?

934
00:58:42,800 --> 00:58:45,200
Mr. Hopper, I have here a record

935
00:58:45,300 --> 00:58:47,400
of your employment
for the last ten years,

936
00:58:47,500 --> 00:58:50,200
a list of the jobs you've held
during that period.

937
00:58:51,900 --> 00:58:54,100
Can you authenticate
it for us, please?

938
00:58:56,400 --> 00:59:01,000
For the record, I showed
the defendant a blank sheet of paper.

939
00:59:01,100 --> 00:59:05,300
Your Honor, I'd like to submit
this blank piece of paper as Exhibit "A."

940
00:59:05,400 --> 00:59:06,900
Objections?

941
00:59:07,900 --> 00:59:09,000
So ordered.

942
00:59:09,100 --> 00:59:13,000
And is this not a complete list

943
00:59:13,200 --> 00:59:15,600
of your financial holdings,
Mr. Hopper?

944
00:59:16,500 --> 00:59:20,800
Naught, aught, goose-egg?

945
00:59:20,900 --> 00:59:24,000
- I was just having a streak of bad luck.
- Yes or no.

946
00:59:24,100 --> 00:59:25,300
Yes.

947
00:59:26,100 --> 00:59:28,800
This streak has apparently lasted
your whole life.

948
00:59:28,900 --> 00:59:30,800
Exhibit "B," Your Honor.

949
00:59:32,400 --> 00:59:37,500
Mr. Hopper, on these sheets
are a list of charges

950
00:59:37,600 --> 00:59:40,500
you've signed for
with the credit cards you received.

951
00:59:41,700 --> 00:59:45,200
Would you mind reading the total
of these charges on the last page for us?

952
00:59:48,300 --> 00:59:51,200
$329,000.69.

953
00:59:51,300 --> 00:59:53,400
I'm sorry, I couldn't quite hear you.

954
00:59:53,500 --> 00:59:59,900
Did you say $329,000.69?
Is that correct?

955
01:00:00,000 --> 01:00:02,000
Yes.

956
01:00:02,100 --> 01:00:04,600
Exhibit "C."

957
01:00:04,700 --> 01:00:09,900
A list of Mr. Hopper's charges
with signed receipts.

958
01:00:10,000 --> 01:00:12,600
And now,
with the court's permission...

959
01:00:16,800 --> 01:00:18,900
Oh, my God!

960
01:00:19,000 --> 01:00:20,000
Do you believe it?

961
01:00:20,200 --> 01:00:21,100
Order!

962
01:00:21,300 --> 01:00:22,200
Order!

963
01:00:22,300 --> 01:00:23,700
Your Honor...

964
01:00:23,800 --> 01:00:24,600
Order.

965
01:00:24,800 --> 01:00:26,100
Let's have some order in here.

966
01:00:26,100 --> 01:00:28,900
The assistant district attorney
is playing the clown.

967
01:00:29,000 --> 01:00:30,500
This is a mockery!

968
01:00:32,700 --> 01:00:37,000
Are all these your cards,
Mr. Hopper?

969
01:00:37,100 --> 01:00:41,100
Well, I'd have to check, Your Honor,
but they appear to be.

970
01:00:41,200 --> 01:00:45,700
Tell me, slugger, how many
would you say there are?

971
01:00:47,100 --> 01:00:48,300
Quite a few, Your Honor.

972
01:00:48,400 --> 01:00:50,800
I can see that. How many?

973
01:00:51,000 --> 01:00:53,800
I know how many I have.

974
01:00:53,900 --> 01:00:55,100
Three.

975
01:00:55,200 --> 01:00:56,400
I have four!

976
01:01:04,000 --> 01:01:05,600
Two hundred and eight.

977
01:01:09,100 --> 01:01:10,400
There you have it.

978
01:01:10,500 --> 01:01:16,600
This unemployed ne'er-do-well
with no resources, no income,

979
01:01:16,700 --> 01:01:20,100
no inheritance, no assets,
and no future,

980
01:01:20,200 --> 01:01:24,400
had 208 credit cards,
ladies and gentlemen.

981
01:01:26,600 --> 01:01:29,200
Exhibit "D," Your Honor.

982
01:01:29,300 --> 01:01:31,100
And the state rests.

983
01:01:33,700 --> 01:01:37,300
I told you he would skin you alive,
and I told you not to take the stand.

984
01:01:37,400 --> 01:01:38,300
What do we do now?

985
01:01:38,400 --> 01:01:40,500
- We make a deal.
- No deal!

986
01:01:41,600 --> 01:01:43,400
I am not gonna admit
I did anything wrong,

987
01:01:43,500 --> 01:01:45,400
I'm not paying 'em back
the rest of my life,

988
01:01:45,500 --> 01:01:47,000
and I'm not giving up the league.

989
01:01:47,100 --> 01:01:49,600
And you're not gonna listen
to your attorney, either.

990
01:01:50,500 --> 01:01:53,000
Maybe you should just
represent yourself.

991
01:01:54,700 --> 01:01:57,500
Maybe I should.

992
01:02:08,300 --> 01:02:12,600
You know, Nicky, I don't want you
to think your uncle's a bad guy,

993
01:02:12,700 --> 01:02:15,600
'cause I didn't mean to take
anything from anybody.

994
01:02:16,200 --> 01:02:18,300
You mean steal?

995
01:02:18,400 --> 01:02:21,000
Look, Nicky, I would never
do anything dishonest.

996
01:02:21,100 --> 01:02:25,400
But Mom says you could go to jail
and end up being somebody's bitch.

997
01:02:27,200 --> 01:02:28,900
Yeah, something like that.

998
01:02:29,900 --> 01:02:32,900
All rise for the Honorable
Rutherford B. Woolsey.

999
01:02:39,200 --> 01:02:41,300
Your Honor, at this time
I'd like the court to know

1000
01:02:41,400 --> 01:02:43,500
that Mr. Hopper
has dismissed me as counsel

1001
01:02:43,500 --> 01:02:45,200
and has chosen
to represent himself.

1002
01:02:45,300 --> 01:02:47,400
Good God, he's fired his lawyer!

1003
01:02:47,500 --> 01:02:49,500
There'll be no outbursts
in this courtroom.

1004
01:02:52,500 --> 01:02:56,100
Is this true, Mr. Hopper?
Do you want to represent yourself?

1005
01:02:56,200 --> 01:02:57,300
Yes, Your Honor.

1006
01:02:57,400 --> 01:03:00,000
Your Honor, Mr. Hopper
practiced law some years ago

1007
01:03:00,100 --> 01:03:01,900
and is perfectly competent to proceed.

1008
01:03:02,000 --> 01:03:06,100
Well, I have no problem with it,
if opposing counsel doesn't mind.

1009
01:03:06,200 --> 01:03:08,800
I most certainly welcome it,
Your Honor.

1010
01:03:16,200 --> 01:03:17,900
I'll need a few days, Your Honor.

1011
01:03:19,200 --> 01:03:21,600
Anything?

1012
01:03:21,700 --> 01:03:22,900
Nothing yet.

1013
01:03:24,100 --> 01:03:25,100
Don't be nervous.

1014
01:03:26,400 --> 01:03:27,800
I'm not nervous.

1015
01:03:28,800 --> 01:03:31,200
Just haven't practiced
law in a while.

1016
01:03:31,300 --> 01:03:33,000
What was your last court case?

1017
01:03:36,400 --> 01:03:39,200
A street vendor
had his license revoked.

1018
01:03:40,600 --> 01:03:42,600
Maybe you should be nervous.

1019
01:03:44,200 --> 01:03:45,900
Here it is. Perfect.

1020
01:03:48,000 --> 01:03:49,800
Right here in the local paper.

1021
01:03:50,800 --> 01:03:51,700
Let me see.

1022
01:04:02,600 --> 01:04:03,400
Miss Thompson?

